CGFloat - class for anyhting to do with UIView

CGPoint - struct with CGFloats
var point = CGPoint(x: 37.0, y: 33.0)

CGSize - with height and width
var size = CGSize(width: 100.0, height: 50.0)

CGRect - rectangle
struct CGRect {
    var origin: CGPoint
    var size: CGSize
}

Units are points
How may pixels per points: var contentScaleFactor: CGFloat

var bounds: CGRect // space's origin and size
frame and center - for UIView positioning

NEVER call draw(CGRect)
setNeedsDisplay()
setNeedsDisplay(_ rect: CGRect) - to set redraw

